{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":7208,"text":"A question I'm often asked is,"},{"time":9168,"text":"where did I get my passion\nfor human rights and justice?"},{"time":14658,"text":"It started early."},{"time":16515,"text":"I grew up in the west of Ireland,"},{"time":18816,"text":"wedged between four brothers,"},{"time":20901,"text":"two older than me and two younger than me."},{"time":23695,"text":"So of course I had to be\ninterested in human rights,"},{"time":26930,"text":"and equality and justice,"},{"time":29459,"text":"and using my elbows!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":31204,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":33041,"text":"And those issues stayed\nwith me and guided me,"},{"time":36054,"text":"and in particular,"},{"time":37704,"text":"when I was elected the first\nwoman President of Ireland,"},{"time":42278,"text":"from 1990 to 1997."},{"time":45539,"text":"I dedicated my presidency"},{"time":48080,"text":"to having a space for those who felt\nmarginalized on the island of Ireland,"},{"time":53561,"text":"and bringing together communities\nfrom Northern Ireland"},{"time":56314,"text":"with those from the Republic,"},{"time":58078,"text":"trying to build peace."},{"time":60465,"text":"And I went as the first Irish president\nto the United Kingdom"},{"time":65739,"text":"and met with Queen Elizabeth II,"},{"time":68749,"text":"and also welcomed to my\nofficial residence --"},{"time":72581,"text":"which we call \"Áras an Uachtaráin,\"\nthe house of the president --"},{"time":76384,"text":"members of the royal family,"},{"time":78654,"text":"including, notably, the Prince of Wales."},{"time":81946,"text":"And I was aware that at the time\nof my presidency,"},{"time":88332,"text":"Ireland was a country beginning\na rapid economic progress."},{"time":93772,"text":"We were a country that was benefiting\nfrom the solidarity of the European Union."},{"time":101607,"text":"Indeed, when Ireland first joined\nthe European Union in 1973,"},{"time":106635,"text":"there were parts of the country\nthat were considered developing,"},{"time":110015,"text":"including my own beloved\nnative county, County Mayo."},{"time":114563,"text":"I led trade delegations\nhere to the United States,"},{"time":118898,"text":"to Japan, to India,"},{"time":121808,"text":"to encourage investment,\nto help to create jobs,"},{"time":125098,"text":"to build up our economy,"},{"time":126448,"text":"to build up our health system,\nour education --"},{"time":128766,"text":"our development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130956,"text":"What I didn't have to do as president"},{"time":134000,"text":"was buy land on mainland Europe,"},{"time":138665,"text":"so that Irish citizens could go there\nbecause our island was going underwater."},{"time":145711,"text":"What I didn't have to think about,"},{"time":147365,"text":"either as president\nor as a constitutional lawyer,"},{"time":150064,"text":"was the implications\nfor the sovereignty of the territory"},{"time":153740,"text":"because of the impact of climate change."},{"time":157309,"text":"But that is what President Tong,\nof the Republic of Kiribati,"},{"time":162104,"text":"has to wake up every morning\nthinking about."},{"time":165470,"text":"He has bought land in Fiji\nas an insurance policy,"},{"time":170752,"text":"what he calls, \"migration with dignity,\""},{"time":174537,"text":"because he knows that his people\nmay have to leave their islands."},{"time":180295,"text":"As I listened to President Tong\ndescribing the situation,"},{"time":185407,"text":"I really felt that this was a problem\nthat no leader should have to face."},{"time":192194,"text":"And as I heard him speak\nabout the pain of his problems,"},{"time":197984,"text":"I thought about Eleanor Roosevelt."},{"time":201703,"text":"I thought about her\nand those who worked with her"},{"time":206103,"text":"on the Commission on Human Rights,\nwhich she chaired in 1948,"},{"time":211205,"text":"and drew up the Universal\nDeclaration of Human Rights."},{"time":216036,"text":"For them, it would have been unimaginable"},{"time":219638,"text":"that a whole country\ncould go out of existence"},{"time":224296,"text":"because of human-induced climate change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227741,"text":"I came to climate change not as\na scientist or an environmental lawyer,"},{"time":232514,"text":"and I wasn't really impressed\nby the images of polar bears"},{"time":236497,"text":"or melting glaciers."},{"time":238131,"text":"It was because of the impact on people,"},{"time":242004,"text":"and the impact on their rights --"},{"time":245101,"text":"their rights to food and safe water,\nhealth, education and shelter."},{"time":250256,"text":"And I say this with humility,"},{"time":254657,"text":"because I came late\nto the issue of climate change."},{"time":258894,"text":"When I served"},{"time":260069,"text":"as UN High Commissioner for Human Rights"},{"time":262093,"text":"from 1997 to 2002,"},{"time":265347,"text":"climate change wasn't\nat the front of my mind."},{"time":267577,"text":"I don't remember making\na single speech on climate change."},{"time":271498,"text":"I knew that there was another\npart of the United Nations --"},{"time":274825,"text":"the UN Convention on Climate Change --"},{"time":277007,"text":"that was dealing with\nthe issue of climate change."},{"time":280752,"text":"It was later when I started\nto work in African countries"},{"time":285136,"text":"on issues of development and human rights."},{"time":288428,"text":"And I kept hearing\nthis pervasive sentence:"},{"time":291714,"text":"\"Oh, but things are so much worse now,\nthings are so much worse.\""},{"time":296502,"text":"And then I explored what was behind that;"},{"time":299892,"text":"it was about changes in the climate --"},{"time":303225,"text":"climate shocks, changes in the weather."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306859,"text":"I met Constance Okollet,"},{"time":308911,"text":"who had formed a women's group\nin Eastern Uganda,"},{"time":312093,"text":"and she told me that\nwhen she was growing up,"},{"time":314744,"text":"she had a very normal life in her village\nand they didn't go hungry,"},{"time":319101,"text":"they knew that the seasons would come\nas they were predicted to come,"},{"time":324454,"text":"they knew when to sow\nand they knew when to harvest,"},{"time":327255,"text":"and so they had enough food."},{"time":330008,"text":"But, in recent years,"},{"time":332357,"text":"at the time of this conversation,"},{"time":334305,"text":"they had nothing\nbut long periods of drought,"},{"time":337559,"text":"and then flash flooding,"},{"time":339234,"text":"and then more drought."},{"time":341280,"text":"The school had been destroyed,"},{"time":342845,"text":"livelihoods had been destroyed,"},{"time":344408,"text":"their harvest had been destroyed."},{"time":346206,"text":"She forms this women's group\nto try to keep her community together."},{"time":351169,"text":"And this was a reality\nthat really struck me,"},{"time":356353,"text":"because of course,\nConstance Okollet wasn't responsible"},{"time":360762,"text":"for the greenhouse gas emissions\nthat were causing this problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364809,"text":"Indeed, I was very struck\nabout the situation in Malawi"},{"time":368975,"text":"in January of this year."},{"time":370881,"text":"There was an unprecedented\nflooding in the country,"},{"time":374032,"text":"it covered about a third of the country,"},{"time":376438,"text":"over 300 people were killed,"},{"time":378628,"text":"and hundreds of thousands\nlost their livelihoods."},{"time":382388,"text":"And the average person in Malawi"},{"time":385508,"text":"emits about 80 kg of CO2 a year."},{"time":391166,"text":"The average US citizen emits\nabout 17.5 metric tons."},{"time":397126,"text":"So those who are suffering\ndisproportionately"},{"time":400841,"text":"don't drive cars, don't have electricity,\ndon't consume very significantly,"},{"time":407706,"text":"and yet they are feeling more and more"},{"time":410888,"text":"the impacts of the changes in the climate,"},{"time":415301,"text":"the changes that are preventing them\nfrom knowing how to grow food properly,"},{"time":419594,"text":"and knowing how\nto look after their future."},{"time":423514,"text":"I think it was really\nthe importance of the injustice"},{"time":431031,"text":"that really struck me very forcibly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434061,"text":"And I know that we're not able\nto address some of that injustice"},{"time":441136,"text":"because we're not on course\nfor a safe world."},{"time":444627,"text":"Governments around the world agreed\nat the conference in Copenhagen,"},{"time":451040,"text":"and have repeated it\nat every conference on climate,"},{"time":454778,"text":"that we have to stay\nbelow two degrees Celsius"},{"time":458262,"text":"of warming above pre-Industrial standards."},{"time":461673,"text":"But we're on course\nfor about four degrees."},{"time":464609,"text":"So we face an existential threat\nto the future of our planet."},{"time":469506,"text":"And that made me realize"},{"time":471150,"text":"that climate change is the greatest threat\nto human rights in the 21st century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477566,"text":"And that brought me then\nto climate justice."},{"time":481225,"text":"Climate justice responds\nto the moral argument --"},{"time":485408,"text":"both sides of the moral argument --"},{"time":487464,"text":"to address climate change."},{"time":489906,"text":"First of all,"},{"time":491081,"text":"to be on the side of those who are\nsuffering most and are most effected."},{"time":495294,"text":"And secondly,"},{"time":496675,"text":"to make sure that they're not left behind\nagain, when we start to move"},{"time":501700,"text":"and start to address climate change\nwith climate action,"},{"time":504533,"text":"as we are doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507834,"text":"In our very unequal world today,"},{"time":510652,"text":"it's very striking how many\npeople are left behind."},{"time":514929,"text":"In our world of 7.2 billion people,\nabout 3 billion are left behind."},{"time":521262,"text":"1.3 billion don't have access\nto electricity,"},{"time":525699,"text":"and they light their homes\nwith kerosene and candles,"},{"time":529227,"text":"both of which are dangerous."},{"time":530926,"text":"And in fact they spend a lot of their\ntiny income on that form of lighting."},{"time":537441,"text":"2.6 billion people cook on open fires --"},{"time":541794,"text":"on coal, wood and animal dung."},{"time":545327,"text":"And this causes\nabout 4 million deaths a year"},{"time":550025,"text":"from indoor smoke inhalation,"},{"time":552271,"text":"and of course, most of those\nwho die are women."},{"time":556792,"text":"So we have a very unequal world,"},{"time":561046,"text":"and we need to change\nfrom \"business as usual.\""},{"time":567125,"text":"And we shouldn't underestimate\nthe scale and the transformative nature"},{"time":573213,"text":"of the change which will be needed,"},{"time":575974,"text":"because we have to go to zero\ncarbon emissions by about 2050,"},{"time":582587,"text":"if we're going to stay below\ntwo degrees Celsius of warming."},{"time":586976,"text":"And that means we have to leave\nabout two-thirds of the known resources"},{"time":592000,"text":"of fossil fuels in the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594564,"text":"It's a very big change,"},{"time":596311,"text":"and it means that obviously,"},{"time":598867,"text":"industrialized countries\nmust cut their emissions,"},{"time":601533,"text":"must become much more energy-efficient,"},{"time":603628,"text":"and must move as quickly as possible\nto renewable energy."},{"time":608199,"text":"For developing countries\nand emerging economies,"},{"time":612603,"text":"the problem and the challenge\nis to grow without emissions,"},{"time":617184,"text":"because they must develop;\nthey have very poor populations."},{"time":620522,"text":"So they must develop without emissions,\nand that is a different kind of problem."},{"time":626590,"text":"Indeed, no country in the world\nhas actually grown without emissions."},{"time":632132,"text":"All the countries have developed\nwith fossil fuels,"},{"time":634560,"text":"and then may be moving\nto renewable energy."},{"time":636882,"text":"So it is a very big challenge,"},{"time":639245,"text":"and it requires the total support\nof the international community,"},{"time":643979,"text":"with the necessary finance and technology,\nand systems and support,"},{"time":648939,"text":"because no country can make itself safe\nfrom the dangers of climate change."},{"time":656007,"text":"This is an issue that requires\ncomplete human solidarity."},{"time":661306,"text":"Human solidarity, if you like,\nbased on self-interest --"},{"time":664667,"text":"because we are all in this together,"},{"time":666971,"text":"and we have to work together"},{"time":668390,"text":"to ensure that we reach\nzero carbon by 2050."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674675,"text":"The good news is that change is happening,"},{"time":677462,"text":"and it's happening very fast."},{"time":680131,"text":"Here in California,"},{"time":681429,"text":"there's a very ambitious\nemissions target to cut emissions."},{"time":685966,"text":"In Hawaii, they're passing legislation"},{"time":688795,"text":"to have 100 percent\nrenewable energy by 2045."},{"time":693731,"text":"And governments are very ambitious\naround the world."},{"time":697731,"text":"In Costa Rica, they have committed\nto being carbon-neutral by 2021."},{"time":703110,"text":"In Ethiopia, the commitment\nis to be carbon-neutral by 2027."},{"time":709921,"text":"Apple have pledged that their factories\nin China will use renewable energy."},{"time":716440,"text":"And there is a race on at the moment"},{"time":719317,"text":"to convert electricity\nfrom tidal and wave power,"},{"time":723278,"text":"in order that we can leave\nthe coal in the ground."},{"time":727521,"text":"And that change is both welcome\nand is happening very rapidly."},{"time":732368,"text":"But it's still not enough,"},{"time":733777,"text":"and the political will\nis still not enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736475,"text":"Let me come back to President Tong\nand his people in Kiribati."},{"time":742077,"text":"They actually could be able to live\non their island and have a solution,"},{"time":748892,"text":"but it would take a lot of political will."},{"time":751600,"text":"President Tong told me\nabout his ambitious idea"},{"time":755772,"text":"to either build up or even float\nthe little islands where his people live."},{"time":763018,"text":"This, of course, is beyond\nthe resources of Kiribati itself."},{"time":767425,"text":"It would require great solidarity\nand support from other countries,"},{"time":771180,"text":"and it would require\nthe kind of imaginative idea"},{"time":775426,"text":"that we bring together when we want\nto have a space station in the air."},{"time":780436,"text":"But wouldn't it be wonderful\nto have this engineering wonder"},{"time":785315,"text":"and to allow a people to remain\nin their sovereign territory,"},{"time":788872,"text":"and be part of the community of nations?"},{"time":792015,"text":"That is the kind of idea\nthat we should be thinking about."},{"time":797681,"text":"Yes, the challenges\nof the transformation we need are big,"},{"time":802479,"text":"but they can be solved."},{"time":805051,"text":"We are actually, as a people,"},{"time":807106,"text":"very capable of coming together\nto solve problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810806,"text":"I was very conscious of this\nas I took part this year"},{"time":814464,"text":"in commemoration of the 70th anniversary"},{"time":818245,"text":"of the end of the Second\nWorld War in 1945."},{"time":823744,"text":"1945 was an extraordinary year."},{"time":827367,"text":"It was a year when the world faced"},{"time":829997,"text":"what must have seemed almost\ninsoluble problems --"},{"time":833548,"text":"the devastation of the world wars,\nparticularly the Second World War;"},{"time":838121,"text":"the fragile peace that had\nbeen brought about;"},{"time":841352,"text":"the need for a whole\neconomic regeneration."},{"time":844643,"text":"But the leaders of that time\ndidn't flinch from this."},{"time":848892,"text":"They had the capacity, they had\na sense of being driven by"},{"time":853246,"text":"never again must the world\nhave this kind of problem."},{"time":857321,"text":"And they had to build structures\nfor peace and security."},{"time":861061,"text":"And what did we get?\nWhat did they achieve?"},{"time":864546,"text":"The Charter of the United Nations,"},{"time":867189,"text":"the Bretton Woods institutions,\nas they're called, The World Bank,"},{"time":870764,"text":"and the International Monetary Fund."},{"time":873225,"text":"A Marshall Plan for Europe,\na devastated Europe,"},{"time":876623,"text":"to reconstruct it."},{"time":878569,"text":"And indeed a few years later,"},{"time":880654,"text":"the Universal Declaration of Human Rights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884364,"text":"2015 is a year that is similar\nin its importance"},{"time":890002,"text":"to 1945, with similar challenges\nand similar potential."},{"time":895377,"text":"There will be two big summits this year:"},{"time":898424,"text":"the first one, in September in New York,"},{"time":901227,"text":"is the summit for the sustainable\ndevelopment goals."},{"time":905071,"text":"And then the summit in Paris in December,\nto give us a climate agreement."},{"time":911365,"text":"The sustainable development goals\nare intended to help countries"},{"time":917716,"text":"to live sustainably,\nin tune with Mother Earth,"},{"time":921850,"text":"not to take out of Mother Earth\nand destroy ecosystems,"},{"time":927200,"text":"but rather, to live in harmony\nwith Mother Earth,"},{"time":930838,"text":"by living under sustainable development."},{"time":934691,"text":"And the sustainable development goals"},{"time":937088,"text":"will come into operation for all countries"},{"time":939497,"text":"on January 1, 2016."},{"time":942814,"text":"The climate agreement --"},{"time":944015,"text":"a binding climate agreement --"},{"time":945555,"text":"is needed because\nof the scientific evidence"},{"time":949243,"text":"that we're on a trajectory\nfor about a four-degree world"},{"time":952184,"text":"and we have to change course\nto stay below two degrees."},{"time":956033,"text":"So we need to take steps\nthat will be monitored and reviewed,"},{"time":961581,"text":"so that we can keep increasing\nthe ambition of how we cut emissions,"},{"time":966003,"text":"and how we move more rapidly\nto renewable energy,"},{"time":969143,"text":"so that we have a safe world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975665,"text":"The reality is that this issue\nis much too important"},{"time":981872,"text":"to be left to politicians\nand to the United Nations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985459,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":986484,"text":"It's an issue for all of us,"},{"time":988086,"text":"and it's an issue where we need\nmore and more momentum."},{"time":992911,"text":"Indeed, the face of\nthe environmentalist has changed,"},{"time":996420,"text":"because of the justice dimension."},{"time":998753,"text":"It's now an issue\nfor faith-based organizations,"},{"time":1001997,"text":"under very good leadership\nfrom Pope Francis,"},{"time":1005193,"text":"and indeed, the Church of England,"},{"time":1006989,"text":"which is divesting from fossil fuels."},{"time":1009456,"text":"It's an issue for the business community,"},{"time":1013238,"text":"and the good news is"},{"time":1014666,"text":"that the business community\nis changing very rapidly --"},{"time":1017600,"text":"except for the fossil fuel industries --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1019809,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1021428,"text":"Even they are beginning\nto slightly change their language --"},{"time":1024748,"text":"but only slightly."},{"time":1025753,"text":"But business is not only moving rapidly\nto the benefits of renewable energy,"},{"time":1030468,"text":"but is urging politicians\nto give them more signals,"},{"time":1033215,"text":"so that they can move even more rapidly."},{"time":1035214,"text":"It's an issue for the trade\nunion movement."},{"time":1037239,"text":"It's an issue for the women's movement."},{"time":1039286,"text":"It's an issue for young people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041388,"text":"I was very struck when I learned\nthat Jibreel Khazan,"},{"time":1047214,"text":"one of the Greensboro Four who had\ntaken part in the Woolworth sit-ins,"},{"time":1052882,"text":"said quite recently that"},{"time":1054420,"text":"climate change is the lunch counter\nmoment for young people."},{"time":1060446,"text":"So, lunch counter moment\nfor young people of the 21st century --"},{"time":1064758,"text":"the sort of real human rights issue\nof the 21st century,"},{"time":1069123,"text":"because he said it is\nthe greatest challenge"},{"time":1071917,"text":"to humanity and justice in our world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076391,"text":"I recall very much\nthe Climate March last September,"},{"time":1080521,"text":"and that was a huge momentum,"},{"time":1082346,"text":"not just in New York,\nbut all around the world."},{"time":1085332,"text":"and we have to build on that."},{"time":1087626,"text":"I was marching with some\nof The Elders family,"},{"time":1090761,"text":"and I saw a placard\na little bit away from me,"},{"time":1095812,"text":"but we were wedged so closely together --"},{"time":1097790,"text":"because after all, there were 400,000\npeople out in the streets of New York --"},{"time":1101489,"text":"so I couldn't quite get to that placard,"},{"time":1103426,"text":"I would have just liked to have been\nable to step behind it,"},{"time":1106531,"text":"because it said, \"Angry Grannies!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1109001,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1110348,"text":"That's what I felt."},{"time":1111826,"text":"And I have five grandchildren now,"},{"time":1115823,"text":"I feel very happy as an Irish grandmother\nto have five grandchildren,"},{"time":1120135,"text":"and I think about their world,"},{"time":1123202,"text":"and what it will be\nlike when they will share that world"},{"time":1126387,"text":"with about 9 billion other people in 2050."},{"time":1131574,"text":"We know that inevitably it will\nbe a climate-constrained world,"},{"time":1136253,"text":"because of the emissions\nwe've already put up there,"},{"time":1139126,"text":"but it could be a world that is much\nmore equal and much fairer,"},{"time":1144547,"text":"and much better for health,\nand better for jobs"},{"time":1147153,"text":"and better for energy security,"},{"time":1149149,"text":"than the world we have now,"},{"time":1151000,"text":"if we have switched sufficiently\nand early enough to renewable energy,"},{"time":1158222,"text":"and no one is left behind."},{"time":1160678,"text":"No one is left behind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1163736,"text":"And just as we've been\nlooking back this year --"},{"time":1167340,"text":"in 2015 to 1945, looking back 70 years --"},{"time":1172871,"text":"I would like to think\nthat they will look back,"},{"time":1175459,"text":"that world will look back\n35 years from 2050,"},{"time":1180332,"text":"35 years to 2015,"},{"time":1183230,"text":"and that they will say,"},{"time":1186072,"text":"\"Weren't they good\nto do what they did in 2015?"},{"time":1190203,"text":"We really appreciate that they took\nthe decisions that made a difference,"},{"time":1195702,"text":"and that put the world\non the right pathway,"},{"time":1198664,"text":"and we benefit now from that pathway,\""},{"time":1201394,"text":"that they will feel that somehow\nwe took our responsibilities,"},{"time":1205299,"text":"we did what was done\nin 1945 in similar terms,"},{"time":1209482,"text":"we didn't miss the opportunity,"},{"time":1211927,"text":"we lived up to our responsibilities."},{"time":1214133,"text":"That's what this year is about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1217688,"text":"And somehow for me,"},{"time":1219062,"text":"it's captured in words of somebody\nthat I admired very much."},{"time":1223380,"text":"She was a mentor of mine,\nshe was a friend,"},{"time":1225737,"text":"she died much too young,"},{"time":1227709,"text":"she was an extraordinary personality,"},{"time":1229738,"text":"a great champion of the environment:"},{"time":1232246,"text":"Wangari Maathai."},{"time":1234627,"text":"Wangari said once,"},{"time":1237277,"text":"\"In the course of history,"},{"time":1239255,"text":"there comes a time\nwhen humanity is called upon"},{"time":1243290,"text":"to shift to a new level of consciousness,"},{"time":1248065,"text":"to reach a higher moral ground.\""},{"time":1252135,"text":"And that's what we have to do."},{"time":1254078,"text":"We have to reach\na new level of consciousness,"},{"time":1257390,"text":"a higher moral ground."},{"time":1259791,"text":"And we have to do it this year\nin those two big summits."},{"time":1264108,"text":"And that won't happen unless\nwe have the momentum"},{"time":1267730,"text":"from people around the world who say:"},{"time":1270901,"text":"\"We want action now,"},{"time":1272445,"text":"we want to change course,"},{"time":1274040,"text":"we want a safe world,"},{"time":1275437,"text":"a safe world for future generations,"},{"time":1277636,"text":"a safe world for our children\nand our grandchildren,"},{"time":1280268,"text":"and we're all in this together.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1282563,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1283747,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}